# Definition of Done

A task is complete **only** when all apply:

## Implementation

- [ ] Scope implemented as specified in sprint/task
- [ ] Architecture rules followed (modular layering, approved stack)
- [ ] Only allowed folders modified
- [ ] No unrelated file changes

## Quality

- [ ] Null safety preserved (Dart/C#)
- [ ] Errors handled with structured codes and user-safe messages
- [ ] Logging appropriate; no sensitive data logged
- [ ] File sizes within review thresholds or refactor planned
- [ ] No `// ignore` or disabled lint without justification

## Security

- [ ] Security reviewed for trust-boundary changes
- [ ] No secrets committed
- [ ] No privileged client writes
- [ ] Correct environment targeted (no silent production default)

## Testing

- [ ] Tests added for behavioural changes
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] Static analysis passes
- [ ] Formatting passes

## Documentation

- [ ] README, schema, protocol, or architecture docs updated as applicable
- [ ] Environment or migration impact documented
- [ ] No TODO blocking critical behaviour

## Review

- [ ] Pull request checklist complete
- [ ] Human code review approved (required for all merges; mandatory for AI-generated code)

## Prohibited "done" states

- Compiles but tests failing
- Placeholder in production path without explicit marking
- Missing documentation for protocol/schema/security changes
- Feature work started before Foundation Completion Gate approval (Version 1+)

See `docs/development/definition_of_done.md` for the full checklist.
